A commercial driver simply identified as John Inebiomanor on Thursday died in a road accident near Obarenren village, along Benin-Siluko Road in Edo State. The accident involved an Audi saloon car marked Edo BEN 539 JN and a white Renault mini truck marked Edo DEG 908 XA. It was gathered that the deceased was driving the Audi car loaded with palm fruits. Eyewitnesses said driver of the truck rammed into the Audi while attempting to avoid a pot hole on the road. The eyewitnesses said the truck rear tyre dragged the car and caused it to summersault several times. Sympathizers had to use axe to cut through the damaged car to remove the lifeless body of the driver. A female passenger in the car sustained severe injuries and was rushed to an undisclosed hospital for medical attention.  